Discipline in Endurance
Examine the discipline of your endurance. Endurance must be directed toward productive goals and expressed in a constructive manner.
Your Flaws are Possibly Not Real

How many of your inadequacies are real? Or, are they really just due to a lack of confidence? We may like to believe they are all real, because that way we can justify not achieving and not meeting our potential. Are achievers more competent, or more persistent? All of us have far more potential than we think we have -- the difference is mostly in persistence.

Break one bad habit today.
Is my endurance and determination focused to help cultivate good habits and break bad ones?
Is it the other way around?
Does my endurance come from strength or weakness?
Does it come out of deep conviction or out of defensiveness?
Am I tenacious out of stubbornness and an unwillingness to acknowledge errors?
Am I invested in certain decisions and unwilling to review them?
Do I use my endurance against itself by being tenacious in my lack of determination?
